.TH VAULT 1 "April 2026" "1.0.0" "Vault CLI Manual"
.SH NAME
vault \- local secure storage and environment variable injector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vault
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIcommand\fR] [\fIarguments\fR...]
.br
.B vault init
[\-f \fIfile\fR] [\-g]
.br
.B vault add
\fIkey\fR [value] [\-g]
.br
.B vault enable-biometrics
.br
.B vault share
.br
.B vault ingest
\fIfile\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBvault\fR is a local, open-source CLI tool designed to eliminate plain-text .env files. 
It utilizes \fBlibsodium\fR for hardware-backed (macOS Keychain) envelope encryption. 
Secrets are decrypted in-memory and injected exclusively into temporary child processes.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init [\-f \fIfile\fR] [\-g]
Initialize a project vault (.env.vault) or a machine-wide global vault. 
Use \fB\-f\fR to provide a specific file (like .zshrc) and \fB\-g\fR to save selected variables into the global machine identity.
The tool automatically identifies likely secrets based on keywords (API, KEY, SDK, etc.).
.TP
.B add \fIkey\fR [value] (alias: \-a)
Interactively add or update a secret key in the local vault. 
Use \fB\-g\fR or \fB\-\-global\fR to target the machine-wide vault (\fI~/.vault/global.vault\fR).
Values are entered via a hidden prompt if not provided as an argument.
.TP
.B enable-biometrics (alias: eb)
Enable biometric authentication (Touch ID) for the global machine identity. This allows you to upgrade an existing password-based identity to use fingerprint authentication.
.TP
.B share
Export current project secrets to a transport-ready file (\fIshared.vault\fR) encrypted with a One-Time Password (OTP).
.TP
.B ingest \fIfile\fR
Decrypt a transport file using an OTP and merge it into the local project vault. The transport file is automatically deleted after a successful ingest.
.TP
.B [command...]
Execute the specified command with decrypted environment variables injected into the process. If no command is provided, it spawns a temporary subshell ($SHELL).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Output the version number.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help information.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B VAULT_MASTER_PASSWORD
If set, the CLI will use this value instead of prompting for the Master Password.
.TP
.B VAULT_SESSION_TOKEN
Used by AI agents to manage secrets during an authorized session.
.SH AUTHOR
Lutfi Garzon
